‚ÄúBetaab Dil‚Äù is a heart-touching romantic Hindi song that brings back the golden era of 90s Bollywood music. Sung and composed by Sarit Dutta, this soulful melody beautifully captures the emotions of love, longing, and separation. The heartfelt lyrics by Dr. Uma Naveen Mehta paint a timeless picture of a betaab (restless) heart waiting for its beloved.

If you miss the charm of classic love songs, ‚ÄúBetaab Dil‚Äù will take you straight back to that nostalgic era of melody and emotion.

üéß Experience ‚ÄúBetaab Dil‚Äù ‚Äî A Pure Hindi Romantic Love Song
Close your eyes, feel the rhythm, and let this song remind you of the beautiful simplicity of true love. Perfect for anyone who believes in eternal romance and misses the soulful tunes of the 90s

snippet.description:
Presenting the official teaser of ek≈ç, directed by Dinjith Ayyathan, following his acclaimed film Kishkindha Kaandam. Written by Bahul Ramesh, ek≈ç marks the final chapter of his Animal Trilogy after Kishkindha Kaandam and Kerala Crime Files: Season 2, forming a collection of three standalone stories sharing a spiritual essence ‚Äî exploring crimes and moral conflicts in a world where animal presence plays a stimulating role. 

The film also marks the maiden production venture of Mr. MRK Jhayaram under his banner Aaradyaa Studios.

snippet.title: Bajido - 4K Video - Gopal Bharwad - Manisha Bharwad - ‡™¨‡™æ‡™ú‡´Ä‡™°‡´ã - Jigar Studio
snippet.description:
Song: Bajido
Singer: Gopal Bharwad, Manisha Bharwad
Artists: Chhaya Thakor, Kuldeep Mishra, Raj Chaudhary
Music: Jackie Gajjar
Lyrics: Govind Bamba
Co - Ordinator: Indar Gamara
D.O.P. - Edit: Montu Rajput
Creative Director: Vishnu Thakor - Adalaj
Producer & Director: Gunvant Thakor
Music Label & Copyright: Jigar Studio

Lyrics Of This Song:

Ho Pataliyo Parono, Pampan Premalo
Baliyo Ne Eto Bajigariyo
Bajido Mane Valo Ne Vat Valo

Ho Tu Hale Utavali, Dharati Dhrujavati
Babbe Bedaliye Bharati Pani
Tari Hare Mari Prityu Bandhani

Ho Muchh No Doro Dekhay Dadhalo Dil No Eto Dariyo
Ho Bajido Maro Rudo Rupalo, Nasibe Mane Maliyo

Ho Tamba Pittal Na Tari Mathe Chhe Bedala
Mare To Tari Hare Chhe Nedala
Bhave Bhav Reshu Aapane Bhela

Ho Ho Bajido Mane Valo Ne Vatvalo


Ho Simade Setar, Zape Chhe Zupada
Ghadu Tara Ghar Na Rotala
Jojo Re Prem Tame Ochho Na Karata
Manigar Man Na Morala

Ho Me To Jodya Hatida Bapor Tana
Lai Aavo Bhat Panida
Ek Bhana Ma Jamashu Aapane Mithuda Bhojaniya

Ho Boli Mobhare Chibari, Aadi Utari Mindaradi
Vayaro Veri Evo Vayo, Apshukan Ni Aendhani

Ho Mand Me Joya Sukh Na Shamana
Tya Dukh Na Dungare Gherya
Man Thi Manya Ene Mari Nakhya

Ho Mara Bajida Ne Have Kon Hamjave


Ho Aankhe Joyelu Kane Padelu
Hotu Nathi Badhu Hachu Re
Bajida Tamane Bhavatu Bhanu
Aaje Aam Kem Thelyu Re

Ho Bharoha Na Bhare Prityu Bandhi
Ganthyu Bandhi Hati Prem Ni
Vachano Bhuli Gai Bhela Revana
Tare Majburi Hati Kem Ni

Ho Ek Ek Shwash Maro Tara Nam No Ur Ma Me To Bharyo
Tara Vagar Ek Pal Na Jivu Tane Bharthar Bhav No Manyo

Ho Khota Re Vem Ma, Bhav Maro Balyo
Haiye Thi Hu To Have Hari Gayo
Aa Bajido Kalaje Kakali Ne Royo

He Toye Mare Man Maro Bajido Vhalo
Aa Bajido Taro Bhule Bhatkayo

snippet.title: Kerala Blasters FC 3-0 Sporting Club Delhi | AIFF Super Cup 2025-26 | Group D | Highlights
snippet.description:
Kerala Blasters FC produced a dominant display to thrash Sporting Club Delhi 3-0 in their second AIFF Super Cup 2025-26 Group D fixture at the GMC Stadium in Bambolim on Monday, November 3, 2025. All the goals came in the first half.

A brace from Koldo Obieta (17‚Äô, 22‚Äô) and Korou Singh‚Äôs acrobatic strike (34‚Äô) sealed a comfortable victory for the Blasters, who now sit top of the group with six points from two matches. The result also confirmed SC Delhi‚Äôs elimination from the tournament, while Kerala Blasters strengthened their bid for a semi-final berth.

Dua gol dari Koldo Obieta (17', 22') dan tendangan akrobatik Korou Singh (34') memastikan kemenangan mudah bagi Blasters, yang kini memuncaki grup dengan enam poin dari dua pertandingan. Match
AUS vs IND ‚Ä¢ 3rd T20I ‚Ä¢ India tour of Australia, 2025
Series: India tour of Australia, 2025
Date: Today
Time: 7:15 PM LOCAL, 8:15 AM GMT

India have never played this format here. The bulk of the T20Is at this venue were played during the 2022 T20 World Cup. Australia have an unbeaten record here in five games having triumphed over Pakistan and once and twice each over West Indies and England. Hobart also has a bit of rolling out absolute batting beauties on occasions and when that happens the scores can get really high. Spinners didn't enjoy a great deal here last BBL but given the quality and variety of India's spinners Australia know they could still pose a challenge.
Welcome to Bellerive Oval, home to Hobart Hurricanes in the BBL - a place where Australia last year unearthed their latest white-ball bully in Mitchell Owen. He smashed two hundreds at this venue opening the batting to finish as the highest run scorer in his debut season. And he can bowl too. There are teams that struggle to produce all-rounders and there is Australia who not only get all-rounders but players who can make a strong impact with both bat and ball. It is also here that Nathan Ellis led the Canes to title victory alongside Tim David.

Squads:
Australia Squad: Mitchell Marsh(c), Travis Head, Josh Inglis(w), Tim David, Mitchell Owen, Marcus Stoinis, Glenn Maxwell, Mahli Beardman, Xavier Bartlett, Nathan Ellis, Matthew Kuhnemann, Sean Abbott, Matthew Short, Josh Philippe, Tanveer Sangha
India Squad: Shubman Gill, Abhishek Sharma, Suryakumar Yadav(c), Tilak Varma, Sanju Samson(w), Shivam Dube, Axar Patel, Harshit Rana, Kuldeep Yadav, Varun Chakaravarthy, Jasprit Bumrah, Arshdeep Singh, Washington Sundar, Rinku Singh, Jitesh Sharma
